---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy";
const description = "MD Home Care's commitment to protecting your privacy and personal information";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="hero min-h-[30vh] bg-base-200">
    <div class="hero-content text-center">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold text-base-content mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-base-content/60">
          Last Updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-AU', {day: 'numeric', month: 'long', year: 'numeric'})}
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content Section -->
  <section class="py-12 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl">
        <div class="card-body prose-mdhomecare">

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>MD Home Care is committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information in accordance with the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs) contained in the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth).</p>
            <p>By using the MD Home Care platform, website, or providing us with your personal information, you consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.</p>
            <p class="mt-4"><strong>Important:</strong> MD Home Care is a connection platform. When you engage with providers through MD Home Care, those providers will also collect and use your information in accordance with their own privacy policies for the purpose of delivering services. This Privacy Policy applies only to information collected by MD Home Care.</p>
          </section>

          <div class="divider"></div>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>MD Home Care may collect the following types of personal information:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Personal details:</strong> Your name, date of birth, contact information, and location</li>
              <li><strong>Support needs:</strong> General information about your disability, age, and support requirements to help match you with appropriate providers</li>
              <li><strong>NDIS information:</strong> Your NDIS plan details, funding arrangements, and participant number (where applicable)</li>
              <li><strong>Contact preferences:</strong> How and when you prefer to be contacted</li>
              <li><strong>Website usage:</strong> Information about how you use the MD Home Care website, collected through cookies and similar technologies</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">Providers in the MD Home Care network may collect additional health information and service records directly from you for the purpose of delivering services. This information is collected and managed by the provider in accordance with their privacy policies.</p>
          </section>

          <div class="divider"></div>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">3. How We Collect Your Information</h2>
            <p>We collect personal information directly from you when you:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Register on the MD Home Care platform</li>
              <li>Complete enquiry or contact forms</li>
              <li>Communicate with us through phone, email, or in person</li>
              <li>Use the MD Home Care website</li>
              <li>Provide feedback or make a complaint</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">We may also collect information from third parties such as:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Support coordinators or plan managers (with your consent)</li>
              <li>The National Disability Insurance Agency (NDIA)</li>
              <li>Your representatives or family members (with your consent)</li>
              <li>Providers in the MD Home Care network (for connection and matching purposes)</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <div class="divider"></div>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use your personal information to:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Connect you with appropriate providers in the MD Home Care network</li>
              <li>Facilitate introductions and referrals to providers</li>
              <li>Communicate with you about provider options and services available</li>
              <li>Improve the MD Home Care platform and develop new features</li>
              <li>Respond to your inquiries and feedback</li>
              <li>Comply with our legal and regulatory obligations</li>
              <li>Conduct quality assurance and platform improvements</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">MD Home Care does not use your information to directly deliver care services. Service delivery is managed by individual providers who have their own obligations regarding use and protection of your information.</p>
          </section>

          <div class="divider"></div>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">5. Disclosure of Your Information</h2>
            <p>We may disclose your personal information to:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Providers in the MD Home Care network for the purpose of connecting you with services</li>
              <li>MD Home Care platform staff who need the information to assist you</li>
              <li>The NDIA and other government agencies as required</li>
              <li>Third-party service providers who assist us in operating the platform (e.g., website hosting, CRM systems)</li>
              <li>Anyone you authorize us to disclose information to</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">When we connect you with a provider, we share only the information necessary for the provider to assess whether they can meet your needs and to facilitate initial contact. More detailed information will be collected directly by the provider if you choose to engage their services.</p>
            <p>We will not disclose your personal information to overseas recipients without your consent, unless required by law.</p>
          </section>

          <div class="divider"></div>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">6. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We take reasonable steps to protect your personal information from misuse, interference, loss, unauthorized access, modification, or disclosure. These steps include:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Using secure servers and encryption for digital information</li>
              <li>Physical security measures for paper-based records</li>
              <li>Staff training on privacy and confidentiality</li>
              <li>Access controls and authentication procedures</li>
              <li>Regular security assessments and updates</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">While we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee the security of information transmitted over the internet. Information shared with providers is subject to their own security measures and privacy practices.</p>
          </section>

          <div class="divider"></div>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">7. Accessing and Correcting Your Information</h2>
            <p>You have the right to access and correct your personal information held by MD Home Care. To request access or corrections, please contact our Privacy Officer using the details provided below.</p>
            <p>We will respond to your request within a reasonable timeframe. In some circumstances, we may charge a reasonable fee for providing access to your information.</p>
            <p>If we refuse your request for access or correction, we will provide you with written reasons and information about how you can complain about the refusal.</p>
            <p class="mt-4">For information held by individual providers (such as service records and detailed health information), you will need to contact the provider directly.</p>
          </section>

          <div class="divider"></div>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">8. Complaints</h2>
            <p>If you believe that MD Home Care has breached your privacy or you have concerns about how we have handled your personal information, please contact our Privacy Officer.</p>
            <p>We will investigate your complaint and respond to you within a reasonable timeframe. If you are not satisfied with our response, you may contact the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC) at <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link link-primary">www.oaic.gov.au</a>.</p>
            <p class="mt-4">For privacy complaints about a provider's handling of your information during service delivery, you should contact the provider directly in the first instance.</p>
          </section>

          <div class="divider"></div>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">9. Changes to Our Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our platform functionality, practices, or legal requirements. The updated policy will be posted on our website, and the revised version will be effective from the date of posting.</p>
          </section>

          <!-- Contact Card -->
          <div class="alert bg-base-200 mt-8">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="stroke-primary shrink-0 w-6 h-6">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold">Contact Our Privacy Officer</h3>
              <p class="text-sm">For any privacy-related inquiries, please <a href="/contact" class="link link-primary">contact us</a> or call <a href="tel:+61863869999" class="link link-primary">08 6386 9999</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
